在[[心理學|心理學]]研究中，'''神經質'''（英語：Neuroticism），或譯'''情绪不稳定性'''等，被認為是一種基本的[[人格特質|人格特質]]。 例如，在人格特質理論的[[五大性格特質|大五人格方法]]中，神經質得分高的人比平均水平更容易[[情緒|情緒]]化，且更容易經驗[[焦慮|焦慮]]、[[擔心|擔心]]、[[恐懼|恐懼]]、[[憤怒|憤怒]]、[[挫折|挫折]]、[[羨慕|羨慕]]、[[妒忌|嫉妒]]、[[內疚|內疚]]、[[抑鬱|沮喪]]、[[孤獨|孤獨]]等[[感覺|感覺]]。<ref name="Thompson">{{cite journal|title=Development and Validation of an International English Big-Five Mini-Markers|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_personality-and-individual-differences_2008-10_45_6/page/542|last=Thompson|first=E.R.|date=October 2008|journal=Personality and Individual Differences|issue=6|doi=10.1016/j.paid.2008.06.013|volume=45|pages=542–548}}</ref> 

神經質指數得分高的人，被認為有患常見[[精神障礙|精神障礙]]（[[情緒障礙|情緒障礙]]、[[焦慮症|焦慮症]]和[[物質使用疾患|物質使用障礙]]等相關部分已被進行研究）<ref name="NeuroticismMA2">{{cite journal|title=Neuroticism's prospective association with mental disorders halves after adjustment for baseline symptoms and psychiatric history, but the adjusted association hardly decays with time: a meta-analysis on 59 longitudinal/prospective studies with 443 313 participants|url=https://zenodo.org/record/895885|journal=Psychological Medicine|issue=14|doi=10.1017/S0033291716001653|year=2016|volume=46|pages=2883–2906|pmid=27523506|author3=Riese, H.|author4=Ormel, J.|author1=Jeronimus B.F.|author2=Kotov, R.|access-date=2021-12-24|archive-date=2019-12-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191229175420/https://zenodo.org/record/895885|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Ormel2013a">{{cite journal|title=Neuroticism and common mental disorders: Meaning and utility of a complex relationship|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_clinical-psychology-review_2013-07_33_5/page/686|journal=Clinical Psychology Review|issue=5|doi=10.1016/j.cpr.2013.04.003|year=2013|volume=33|pages=686–697|pmc=4382368|pmid=23702592|author3=Kotov, M.|author4=Riese, H.|author5=Bos, E.H.|author6=Hankin, B.|author1=Ormel J.|author2=Jeronimus, B.F.}}</ref>，以及[[精神官能症|精神官能症]]的風險<ref>{{Cite book|last=Carducci|first=Bernardo J|date=2009-02-20|title=The Psychology of Personality: Viewpoints, Research, and Applications|isbn=978-1-4051-3635-8|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=1gJPXv5wQbIC&pg=PA174|pages=173–174}}</ref>。<!--—symptoms that traditionally have been called [[神经症|神经症]].-->

